              },
              "displayName": "Tanping Wang",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "body": "[~jlowe]  What the application developers need is a free yet default way of grabbing all the yarn logs, for example.  Certainly there could be scripts build to grab the logs, but Hadoop should contain a tool set that provides all the yarn logs related with one job.  This does not include any other Hadoop services like Hive, Pig or Oozie, but just Hadoop itself.  Thoughts?",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=tanping",
              "name": "tanping",
              "key": "tanping",
              "avatarUrls": {
